bio4enviro grades

Purpose

To explore grades as mechanism to learn.
ID is the final 5 digits in student ID.

Book reviews

library(tidyverse)
#read in evals
reviews_complete <- read_csv("data/2022/reviews.csv")

#calculate totals
reviews_complete <- reviews_complete %>%
  mutate(total = rowSums(.[4:13]))

#tidy up columns and prep unique ID
reviews <- reviews_complete %>%
  mutate(ID = str_sub(student.ID, start = -5)) %>%
  select(ID, everything(), -student.ID, -surname, -name, - comments) %>%
  na.exclude(.)
#table of results
library(DT)
datatable(reviews, rownames = FALSE, options = list(pageLength = length(reviews$ID)))
#parse out comments only
comments <- reviews_complete %>%
  mutate(ID = str_sub(student.ID, start = -5)) %>%
  select(ID, comments) %>%
  na.exclude(.)

#table of observations/comments
datatable(comments, rownames = FALSE, options = list(pageLength = length(comments$ID)))
#mean of test
mreviews <- mean(reviews$total)
